quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  7,85,"And to (the people of) Madyan (Midian), (We sent) their brother Shu‘aib. He said: "
  7,86,""
  7,87,"",footnotes:1:{7:87}:
  8,19,"(O disbelievers) if you ask for a judgement, now has the judgement come unto you; and if you cease (to do wrong), it will be better for you, and if you return (to the attack), so shall We return, and your forces will be of no avail to you, however numerous they be; and verily, Allâh is with the believers."
  8,20,"O you who believe! Obey Allâh and His Messenger, and turn not away from him (i.e. Messenger Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) while you are hearing."
  8,21,"And be not like those who say: "